	<h2>What About Cookies and IP Addresses?</h2>
	<ul>
	    <li>Cookies are alphanumeric identifiers that we transfer to your computer's hard drive through your Web browser to enable our systems to recognize your browser and allow storage of information that you have inserted during visits. We log IP addresses, which are the locations of computers or networks on the Internet, and analyze them for systems administration and troubleshooting purposes. We may also aggregate the number of page hits and collect other data in order to track the popularity and use of certain pages and improve the quality of our site.</li>
	    <li>The Help portion of the toolbar on most browsers will tell you how to prevent your browser from accepting new cookies, how to have the browser notify you when you receive a new cookie, or how to disable cookies altogether. However, because cookies allow us to manage donor campaigns more effectively and assist charitable giving, we recommend that you leave them turned on.</li>
	</ul>


	<h2>Does AlumniFidelity Share the Information It Receives?</h2>

	<p>Information about you is an important part of our business, and we are not in the business of selling it to others. We may share your only as described herein with (i) our vendors who have a need to know such information to process transactions, analyze data, update the website, conduct legal compliance and evaluation, perform marketing and data management services, provide customer service and similar assistance, (ii) charitable organizations and other entities to which you make donations through this site, (iii) any legal or governmental authorities to which we are required to report, as well as (iv) creators of fundraising campaigns who receive reports about donations made through the web pages they create, which include the dates, amounts, and recipients of these contributions.  AlumniFidelity may also share or transfer data that has been aggregated, following analysis, that does not include individual information.</p>

	<ul>
	    <li><strong>Business Transfers</strong>:  As AlumniFidelity expands, we might sell or buy stores, subsidiaries, or develop other business units. In such transactions, customer information generally is one of the transferred business assets but remains subject to the promises made in any pre-existing Privacy Notice (unless, of course, the customer consents otherwise). Also, in the event that AlumniFidelity or substantially all of its assets or equity are acquired, customer information will of course be one of the transferred assets and/or subject to some diligence by an acquirer.</li>
